# Mobile i18n (`@comfort-b2b/mobile`)

i18next + react-i18next with EN + RU. Init lives in `src/i18n/i18n.ts`
(`initReactI18next`, inline resources, no async backend), imported once for its
side effect from `App.tsx`. Use the `useTranslation()` hook in components.

## Typed `t()` without `as const`
Resources are JSON bundles (`en.json`/`ru.json`). The `i18next`
`CustomTypeOptions` augmentation (in `i18n.ts`) types keys off `typeof en` - a
JSON import preserves the key structure, so NO `as const` is needed (the
repo-wide `assertionStyle: "never"` rule bans assertions). Keep `ru.json` in
parity with `en.json`; `i18n.test.ts` enforces identical key sets.

## Error codes -> localized messages
`localizeApiError(error)` maps a typed `ApiError` to a `errors.<CODE>`
translation key + interpolation values, via an exhaustive `switch` with a
`const _: never` guard (adding an `ErrorCode` is a compile error until handled
here AND translated in both bundles).

## Stable analytics labels vs translated display labels
`ORDER_OPTIONS[].label` stays English - it is the stable string sent in the
analytics payload. The UI displays each option via the localized
`options.<id>` key (ids are a typed `OptionId` union so the key is type-checked).
Never localize data sent to the backend/analytics.

## Default language
`i18n.ts` starts in `DEFAULT_LANGUAGE` ("en") - no device-locale auto-detection.
Users switch language in-app via `LanguageSwitcher`.
